This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One. He discusses the President's visit to the hospital and memorial service following the shooting of Congresswoman Gabrielle Giffords. Gibbs gives details of the President's interaction with Giffords' husband and friends, including her opening her eye and raising her arm in response to her husband's request. He also mentions that the President had been working on his speech for the memorial service throughout the day. Gibbs mentions that the President seemed emotional and touched by his meetings with everyone throughout the day. He also mentions that the First Lady was moved by the speech and talks about the impact of the shooting on parents and the difficulty of finding answers to such senseless acts. The press gaggle ends with a discussion about the President's schedule for the next day.